Author: Hollowman9000#3344
Content: Verus is preparing PBaaS, possible test chain launch today

Author: Hollowman9000#3344
Content: ‚Äúwe have enhanced the Komodo crypto-conditions quite a lot in order to implement PBaaS. Verus already supports enhanced crypto-conditions, and we have advanced quite a lot since we implemented the nothing at stake solution using crypto-conditions. at this point, the Verus crypto-conditions have much more capability than their starting point. we are wondering if we should call them their own thing, as implementing PBaaS would be quite difficult without our enhancements. I am looking forward to seeing if their Python-cc system will be good for applications developers. if so, we will support that at some point as well.‚Äù

Author: Hollowman9000#3344
Content: ‚Äúhonestly, i don't actually see any project doing what we will soon release, and it is easy to confuse all the discussion of BaaS with PBaaS, which is en extension of the core blockchain distributed consensus protocols that allows a system of loosely connected chains to function securely in a decentralized manner. I think what we are doing is very different from Red Fox Labs‚Äù

Author: Hollowman9000#3344
Content: ‚Äúthis is actually a major development, and though I am working nonstop on it rather than explaining, we will soon be able to explain in more detail and let the world know that we have something, not just unique, but that truly advances the crypto industry and enables many new use cases‚Äù
